Matplotlib â€“ good for basic plotting

Seaborn â€“ built on Matplotlib, better aesthetics, ideal for EDA

Plotly â€“ for interactive plots (especially maps and dashboards)

Pandas â€“ for quick .plot() based charts

GeoPandas or folium â€“ for geographical maps (if working with lat/long or countries)

